Comment: RDS does not keep track of this. If you forgot the value you specified on instance creation, you can set the New Master Password when you modify your instance

RDS sometimes includes the port with your endpoint: it may look like myinstance.123456789012.us-west-2.rds.amazonaws.com:3306 (colon-separated host and port). Keep track of your port if it’s not 3306, otherwise we’re only interested in the host
